The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Policy plea
                                                                                                               Policy plea
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Bhubaneswar, June 8: The states veteran academics and experts have pressed for the formation of a state council of higher education.        
	A council of higher education needs to be formed to formulate a state-level education policy said Dhanada Mishra of Human Development Foundation that organised the event, attended by the higher education secretary M.S. Padhi, vice-chancellor of Biju Patnaik University of Technology .N. Mohanty and his counterpart in Utkal University, Binayak Rath.         
	Experts discussed the issue at a programme on education challenges in Orissa.              
	Through an elaborate presentation on higher education in the country, Padma Shri K.L. Chopra called for wide-range of reforms at a national-level with the Centre being presented the accreditation authority. He strongly recommended the state government to create its state council for higher education and develop a state policy at the earliest with an aim of creating global professionals.        
	Padma Bibhusan Trilochan Pradhan said the national-level principles, policies and global developments in education need to be applied at a local context.        
	State higher education minister Debi Prasad Mishra sought the co-operation of all stakeholders in order to come up with a roadmap for the future. The panel reviewed the present challenges and recommended urgent reforms to achieve the Vision 2020 set forth by the knowledge commission.        
	The experts felt that the commission should focus on universal access, (well distributed opportunities), equity (reflecting upon societys composition of SC, ST, minority and women) and affordability (no deserving students should be deprived for financial reason).                                                                                                                                                                           
